WEBVTT

1
00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:17.666
Oh. good morning.

2
00:00:17.750 --> 00:00:19.416
-Hi. Dad.
-How are you?

3
00:00:19.500 --> 00:00:21.958
-Ah. no. we are good.
-Hello. dear husband.

4
00:00:22.041 --> 00:00:25.250
-Hello.
-You came right on time.

5
00:00:25.333 --> 00:00:30.583
I just reserved a table for us
for the Ivory Oasis dinner.

6
00:00:30.666 --> 00:00:32.000
so everything is ready.

7
00:00:32.916 --> 00:00:35.041
This is the first time
I'm hearing about this.

8
00:00:36.041 --> 00:00:38.250
Uh. what do you mean
it's your first time hearing about it?

9
00:00:38.333 --> 00:00:40.291
-I told you about this.
-When?

10
00:00:40.375 --> 00:00:42.875
No. Joyce. you didn't tell me.

11
00:00:42.958 --> 00:00:47.541
You must've forgotten. you know.
like how you forgot my birthday.

12
00:00:47.625 --> 00:00:50.083
-Seriously? That's what we're doing now?
-Mm-mmm.

13
00:00:50.166 --> 00:00:51.166
-Knock. knock.
-Leave it.

14
00:00:51.250 --> 00:00:53.333
-I was just saying.
-Morning. morning. family.

15
00:00:53.416 --> 00:00:54.583
My love.

16
00:00:55.291 --> 00:00:57.000
So people just show up here in my house…

17
00:00:57.083 --> 00:00:59.083
-…without the decency to knock.
-Wow.

18
00:00:59.166 --> 00:01:00.166
-Um.
-Whoa.

19
00:01:00.958 --> 00:01:02.000
-Goodness.
-Here…

20
00:01:02.958 --> 00:01:07.250
-is an invite to the twins' christening.
-Wow.

21
00:01:07.333 --> 00:01:09.291
I'd love it if you could all come.

22
00:01:09.375 --> 00:01:11.916
Yeah. of course. Of course.

23
00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:13.458
There's a dress code.

24
00:01:13.541 --> 00:01:15.625
All those that are closest to my heart.

25
00:01:15.708 --> 00:01:19.291
I mean. those who are loved by me.
my children.

26
00:01:19.375 --> 00:01:23.208
you guys as well.
you will be dressed in cream.

27
00:01:23.291 --> 00:01:25.583
-Oh. cream? Wow.
-Mm-hmm.

28
00:01:25.666 --> 00:01:27.625
-And others?
-Others what?

29
00:01:27.708 --> 00:01:29.000
What will they wear?

30
00:01:29.083 --> 00:01:32.541
They'll just wear what they usually wear
at church on a Sunday.

31
00:01:34.500 --> 00:01:35.958
Okay. thank you.

32
00:01:36.041 --> 00:01:37.833
Enjoy your breakfast.

33
00:01:37.916 --> 00:01:40.666
-I have somewhere to be. I'll see you.
-Okay.

34
00:01:40.750 --> 00:01:42.291
"Those closest to my heart."

35
00:01:42.375 --> 00:01:46.083
Well. you can miss me at that christening.

36
00:01:46.166 --> 00:01:49.250
Listen here.
That christening is for your sisters.

37
00:01:50.333 --> 00:01:53.958
We're all going there as a family.
Do you understand?

38
00:01:54.041 --> 00:01:57.666
Well. that means
I'll be in my Sunday best.

39
00:02:17.333 --> 00:02:20.250
I really take care of you guys.

40
00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:25.958
Who else have you seen buying lunch
worth 150 rand in this township?

41
00:02:27.791 --> 00:02:30.083
The new babies get special treatment.

42
00:02:30.166 --> 00:02:31.875
-Hmm.
-What's going on?

43
00:02:31.958 --> 00:02:34.625
Oh. wow. Matipa's kids are being baptised.

44
00:02:35.166 --> 00:02:37.708
-Oh? Wow.
-Mm-hmm.

45
00:02:38.208 --> 00:02:39.500
What are you holding?

46
00:02:40.666 --> 00:02:43.666
Oh. Dad just forgot his fancy pen.

47
00:02:43.750 --> 00:02:44.791
Oh.

48
00:02:44.875 --> 00:02:46.625
I guess old age doesn't announce itself.

49
00:02:46.708 --> 00:02:48.083
Stop it with your drama.

50
00:02:48.166 --> 00:02:50.375
Whoa. It's just a pen.

51
00:02:50.458 --> 00:02:52.125
We all know dad is very careful

52
00:02:52.208 --> 00:02:55.166
not to leave anything
that belongs to him here. right?

53
00:02:55.791 --> 00:02:57.833
How about you and I go to the mall?

54
00:02:58.875 --> 00:03:00.333
We're getting beautiful clothes.

55
00:03:00.416 --> 00:03:02.708
I want you to look good
for this christening at the Matipas'.

56
00:03:02.791 --> 00:03:05.250
The twins must be so important.

57
00:03:05.875 --> 00:03:07.750
while we remain hidden.

58
00:03:07.833 --> 00:03:09.833
We have to hide in the shadows.

59
00:03:09.916 --> 00:03:12.791
-No ways. Mom. Why?
-Oh. Sarah.

60
00:03:13.583 --> 00:03:15.708
Well. you're not forced to go. my child.

61
00:03:15.791 --> 00:03:17.791
You can stay if you don't want to.

62
00:03:21.916 --> 00:03:23.791
-So what about your lunch?
-No!

63
00:03:31.541 --> 00:03:34.291
So there's no other venue we can use?

64
00:03:37.458 --> 00:03:38.708
So there's nothing?

65
00:03:40.875 --> 00:03:41.916
Okay.

66
00:03:43.333 --> 00:03:44.500
No. it's fine.

67
00:03:47.416 --> 00:03:48.666
Bye.

68
00:03:49.666 --> 00:03:51.625
Well. the twins are sleeping.

69
00:03:52.375 --> 00:03:55.083
The venue double-booked themselves.

70
00:03:55.791 --> 00:04:00.125
-So we don't have a venue for the party.
-Those idiots.

71
00:04:00.208 --> 00:04:01.500
How do they double-book?

72
00:04:04.958 --> 00:04:08.541
My first event as a mother
and a part of the Gomora family.

73
00:04:08.625 --> 00:04:10.083
and this is what happens.

74
00:04:10.583 --> 00:04:11.583
You know what?

75
00:04:13.125 --> 00:04:14.875
We'll have it at my place.

76
00:04:14.958 --> 00:04:16.500
at my house.

77
00:04:16.583 --> 00:04:19.333
Where will Joyce be when that happens?

78
00:04:19.416 --> 00:04:21.000
She'll be strong.

79
00:04:24.208 --> 00:04:25.208
And then?

80
00:04:26.208 --> 00:04:28.541
Jo?

81
00:04:29.583 --> 00:04:30.916
Jonasi!

82
00:04:31.000 --> 00:04:35.583
So. Joyce agreed for you to have
your kids' party at her house?

83
00:04:35.666 --> 00:04:36.916
-Why?
-I don't know.

84
00:04:37.000 --> 00:04:39.375
Maybe this is her way of showing me

85
00:04:39.458 --> 00:04:42.458
that she's ready to put everything
that has happened in the past

86
00:04:42.541 --> 00:04:44.166
so we can move on with our lives.

87
00:04:44.250 --> 00:04:45.541
-Joyce.
-Oh.

88
00:04:46.166 --> 00:04:47.791
You look so beautiful.

89
00:04:47.875 --> 00:04:50.000
-That dress looks good on you.
-Enough about the dress.

90
00:04:50.083 --> 00:04:51.125
What's going on here?

91
00:04:51.208 --> 00:04:53.791
Oh. uh. the twins' christening party
will be here.

92
00:04:54.375 --> 00:04:55.375
-Jonasi…
-Yes?

93
00:04:55.458 --> 00:04:56.875
Don't you dare. Don't provoke me.

94
00:04:56.958 --> 00:04:59.250
-Provoke you?
-What do you mean the party will be here?

95
00:04:59.333 --> 00:05:03.041
The venue was Hibiscus Manor.
How's my house involved in all of this?

96
00:05:03.125 --> 00:05:05.708
The venue was double-booked.
What were we supposed to do?

97
00:05:05.791 --> 00:05:08.250
What does the double-booking
have to do with me. Jo?

98
00:05:08.333 --> 00:05:10.833
-Come on.
-Jonasi. you're trying to tell me that…

99
00:05:11.583 --> 00:05:13.916
-Mmm.
-…you couldn't consult with me first.

100
00:05:14.000 --> 00:05:15.666
as your wife. before doing all this?

101
00:05:15.750 --> 00:05:20.833
Joyce. I tried speaking to you last night.
and you weren't listening to me.

102
00:05:52.291 --> 00:05:53.625
-Wow.
-You're all so beautiful.

103
00:05:54.250 --> 00:05:55.916
They didn't even tell us the theme.

104
00:05:56.000 --> 00:05:58.541
Even the ballerina's are dressed in white.
We're the only ones…

105
00:05:58.625 --> 00:05:59.791
That doesn't matter. We're here now.

106
00:05:59.875 --> 00:06:02.625
Wait. Mom. Tell me. Was I baptised?

107
00:06:03.500 --> 00:06:05.375
Ah. Sarah. My goodness.

108
00:06:05.458 --> 00:06:08.041
My love. it's not about you.

109
00:06:09.083 --> 00:06:10.875
It's about the twins. Please.

110
00:06:12.458 --> 00:06:13.750
-Sarah.
-Yes?

111
00:06:14.541 --> 00:06:18.458
Just look at your father.
Do you think he's mentally okay?

112
00:06:18.541 --> 00:06:21.666
Look at him. He's acting holier-
than-thou in front of all of these people.

113
00:06:21.750 --> 00:06:24.708
They have no idea
how he treats us like dogs.

114
00:06:24.791 --> 00:06:25.791
Ugh.

115
00:06:25.875 --> 00:06:27.625
That's your brother.

116
00:06:30.166 --> 00:06:32.791
-Can we have a word?
-I'll be back. Okay?

117
00:06:32.875 --> 00:06:35.083
You have some nerve.

118
00:06:35.166 --> 00:06:38.958
You have the nerve to organise parties
at my house without my knowledge?

119
00:06:39.458 --> 00:06:40.916
-You didn't know?
-Cut the act.

120
00:06:41.000 --> 00:06:43.791
It's not an act. Joyce.
I thought Jo told you.

121
00:06:43.875 --> 00:06:46.041
-You had no right--
-Whoa. whoa. whoa.

122
00:06:46.125 --> 00:06:47.333
The right?

123
00:06:48.166 --> 00:06:50.541
Let me remind you
in case you have forgotten.

124
00:06:50.625 --> 00:06:53.208
This is the twins' home too.

125
00:06:53.750 --> 00:06:55.166
How can I forget?

126
00:06:55.250 --> 00:06:59.250
You're always here in my ear constantly
every day reminding me about it.

127
00:06:59.333 --> 00:07:04.125
You know. I really thought that
you made this nice gesture

128
00:07:04.208 --> 00:07:07.333
-to show you have accepted my children.
-Oh.

129
00:07:07.416 --> 00:07:10.291
I guess it's obvious
I was wrong about that.

130
00:07:10.375 --> 00:07:13.875
Oh. you're definitely wrong about that.
Are we clear? Absolutely wrong.

131
00:07:13.958 --> 00:07:15.500
Now. listen here.

132
00:07:15.583 --> 00:07:17.958
There's one problem with you.

133
00:07:18.041 --> 00:07:20.500
You're forgetting that you're here

134
00:07:20.583 --> 00:07:24.708
because I woke up one morning
and decided to allow it.

135
00:07:24.791 --> 00:07:26.375
-Wow.
-I had your life

136
00:07:26.458 --> 00:07:28.958
in the palm of my hand. Matipa.

137
00:07:29.041 --> 00:07:30.625
Have you seen what
they're saying on social media?

138
00:07:30.708 --> 00:07:33.375
-What are they saying?
-They're saying you're a gold-digging

139
00:07:33.458 --> 00:07:34.791
home-wrecker.

140
00:07:34.875 --> 00:07:38.208
Hmm? And that doesn't go away.

141
00:07:38.291 --> 00:07:42.666
You see. those kids? They'll grow up
one day and read about it.

142
00:07:42.750 --> 00:07:46.916
They'll see for themselves
what a home-wrecker their mother was.

143
00:07:49.416 --> 00:07:50.541
Disgusting.

144
00:07:51.541 --> 00:07:53.041
Friend.

145
00:07:53.666 --> 00:07:54.666
Are you okay?

146
00:07:54.750 --> 00:07:57.333
-Joyce. please. Let's go inside.
-Mom.

147
00:07:57.416 --> 00:07:58.750
Mom. please stop.

148
00:08:01.083 --> 00:08:02.166
What is it?

149
00:08:02.250 --> 00:08:04.458
-It's your mother.
-What happened?

150
00:08:04.541 --> 00:08:06.625
Dude. You-You know what…

151
00:08:06.708 --> 00:08:07.708
Wait a minute.

152
00:08:09.333 --> 00:08:11.208
Who's Ashley and who's Hayley?

153
00:08:11.291 --> 00:08:13.125
You still can't tell them apart?

154
00:08:13.208 --> 00:08:14.750
-Are you judging me?
-Okay. wait.

155
00:08:14.833 --> 00:08:18.000
-This is Ashley and this is Hayley.
-Okay.

156
00:08:18.083 --> 00:08:19.875
The thing about Hayley is…

157
00:08:19.958 --> 00:08:22.208
Oh. I need Hayley's pink pacifier.

158
00:08:22.791 --> 00:08:24.625
-Yeah.
-How do you know about the pink pacifier?

159
00:08:24.708 --> 00:08:28.458
Uh. I've been… I've been visiting them.

160
00:08:28.541 --> 00:08:29.958
I'm their big brother.

161
00:08:30.041 --> 00:08:32.166
-Hmm.
-They are your sisters too. Mpume.

162
00:08:33.000 --> 00:08:35.000
-I know.
-Yes. Give it to her.

163
00:08:35.916 --> 00:08:37.333
so that she'll like you. Give it to her.

164
00:08:37.416 --> 00:08:38.958
So she doesn't like me now?

165
00:08:39.041 --> 00:08:40.041
As I was saying.

166
00:08:40.125 --> 00:08:41.708
-that idiot was getting married.
-Uh-huh.

167
00:08:41.791 --> 00:08:43.958
He didn't even show up
for his own wedding.

168
00:08:44.041 --> 00:08:45.416
-He wasn't there? Wow.
-No.

169
00:08:45.500 --> 00:08:47.708
Are you well. Jonasi?

170
00:08:47.791 --> 00:08:49.583
May I have a word with you. please?

171
00:08:50.416 --> 00:08:53.833
-Bro. give me a moment.
-All right.

172
00:08:53.916 --> 00:08:54.916
Moment.

173
00:08:55.583 --> 00:08:56.916
What do we have there?

174
00:08:57.000 --> 00:08:58.000
-Jonasi.
-Hmm?

175
00:08:58.083 --> 00:09:00.750
You know things were left on
a bad note between me and you.

176
00:09:01.458 --> 00:09:05.000
And you haven't bothered yourself
to call me or at least call Sarah.

177
00:09:05.083 --> 00:09:08.000
Do you think this is the right time?

178
00:09:08.583 --> 00:09:09.583
Or the right place?

179
00:09:09.666 --> 00:09:10.750
Oh.

180
00:09:11.250 --> 00:09:13.750
When?
This is the only time we have to talk.

181
00:09:13.833 --> 00:09:15.041
So. you can explain to me.

182
00:09:15.541 --> 00:09:16.916
We'll talk later.

183
00:09:17.625 --> 00:09:18.625
Oh?

184
00:09:19.541 --> 00:09:20.541
Jonasi.

185
00:09:21.333 --> 00:09:23.208
-As I was saying. Brother.
-Yes.

186
00:09:23.291 --> 00:09:25.041
-Talk brother.
-I see you're eyeing someone.

187
00:09:27.791 --> 00:09:30.625
-You drink a lot.
-Pour. pour that into your mocktails.

188
00:09:32.375 --> 00:09:35.666
-Guys. I have some news.
-Yes.

189
00:09:35.750 --> 00:09:38.458
Bongs's parents are leaving next week.

190
00:09:38.541 --> 00:09:41.583
-and I am planning on popping my cherry.
-There you go.

191
00:09:41.666 --> 00:09:43.416
That's what a woman does.

192
00:09:43.500 --> 00:09:46.000
So. how do you want your first time to be?

193
00:09:46.083 --> 00:09:48.583
I want it to be magical.

194
00:09:48.666 --> 00:09:50.333
-Okay. Hmm.
-And memorable.

195
00:09:50.416 --> 00:09:52.250
-Okay.
-Fantastic.

196
00:09:52.333 --> 00:09:54.625
Hold it right there.
I have the right thing for you.

197
00:09:55.958 --> 00:09:58.208
-Let me take it out for you.
-Whoa.

198
00:09:58.291 --> 00:09:59.583
Let me plug you.

199
00:09:59.666 --> 00:10:01.541
You go around carrying panties?

200
00:10:01.625 --> 00:10:04.875
When you go to Bonginkosi wearing this…

201
00:10:05.583 --> 00:10:07.208
he'll definitely be thanking the Lord.

202
00:10:07.291 --> 00:10:08.666
That's not all.

203
00:10:08.750 --> 00:10:09.916
It even has pearls.

204
00:10:10.958 --> 00:10:12.916
-I also have fresh cream.
-Lindani.

205
00:10:13.000 --> 00:10:14.916
Do you girls know where to put this?

206
00:10:15.666 --> 00:10:18.583
-Strategic places.
-No. no. no. You know what?

207
00:10:18.666 --> 00:10:20.375
-It's giving loose vibes.
-Shut up

208
00:10:20.458 --> 00:10:21.833
-and take the cream.
-I don't want it.

209
00:10:21.916 --> 00:10:23.291
What do you think. Sarah?

210
00:10:23.375 --> 00:10:25.083
Hell no. Sex is overrated. Lindani.

211
00:10:25.166 --> 00:10:26.250
-Ugh.
-Mm-mmm.

212
00:10:26.333 --> 00:10:29.791
And. Mpume. why can't you wait
for marriage? What's the rush?

213
00:10:29.875 --> 00:10:31.791
Bongs is my true love.

214
00:10:31.875 --> 00:10:34.333
It's not like I'm throwing away
my virginity by giving it up to him.

215
00:10:34.416 --> 00:10:37.583
You're certainly not. my dear.
Because he is your man after all.

216
00:10:37.666 --> 00:10:40.125
Goodness.
Something you should know. girls.

217
00:10:40.208 --> 00:10:43.250
is that if you don't give it up.
he won't stay.

218
00:10:43.333 --> 00:10:44.625
Well. Bongs…

219
00:10:45.208 --> 00:10:47.750
He's understanding. he's very gentle.

220
00:10:47.833 --> 00:10:49.208
Bongs would never cheat on me.

221
00:10:49.875 --> 00:10:51.375
He's nothing like my father.

222
00:10:51.458 --> 00:10:54.166
You're certainly right.

223
00:10:54.250 --> 00:10:55.833
Your father is something else.

224
00:10:56.375 --> 00:10:59.375
Well. men like
to tap and go though. but okay.

225
00:11:02.500 --> 00:11:05.750
Oh my word. Lindani.

226
00:11:07.250 --> 00:11:08.875
Do you need anything?

227
00:11:08.958 --> 00:11:10.708
I'm fine.

228
00:11:18.875 --> 00:11:20.166
Yes. I'm fine.

229
00:11:21.250 --> 00:11:22.541
It's just the tequila.

230
00:11:26.291 --> 00:11:28.916
My goodness. Hey. hey. hey.

231
00:11:29.000 --> 00:11:30.750
-What is it? Let me see.
-Wait.

232
00:11:30.833 --> 00:11:32.625
Look at this beauty.

233
00:11:32.708 --> 00:11:35.458
You see this?
This is the girl I'm talking about.

234
00:11:35.541 --> 00:11:37.791
This girl. we need to make her Mrs Gomora.

235
00:11:37.875 --> 00:11:41.875
Ah. don't tell me
about Mihlali. man. Please.

236
00:11:41.958 --> 00:11:44.458
You know who Mrs Gomora is going to be.

237
00:11:45.166 --> 00:11:46.500
-Nah.
-Wait.

238
00:11:47.125 --> 00:11:48.750
Here we go.

239
00:11:48.833 --> 00:11:50.125
Um. hi.

240
00:11:51.250 --> 00:11:52.291
Hi.

241
00:11:52.375 --> 00:11:54.250
What's wrong? You don't look okay.

242
00:11:55.333 --> 00:11:57.875
Yeah. I just feel a bit nauseous.

243
00:11:58.708 --> 00:12:00.125
Oh. I'm sorry. Sorry.

244
00:12:00.208 --> 00:12:03.666
Hmm. how about we go inside

245
00:12:03.750 --> 00:12:06.750
and I'll make you some ginger tea
or anything.

246
00:12:07.541 --> 00:12:08.708
Thank you.

247
00:12:12.000 --> 00:12:15.375
I can see that X is not here today.

248
00:12:15.875 --> 00:12:17.125
Is he not coming?

249
00:12:17.208 --> 00:12:20.125
We're going through something right now.

250
00:12:21.166 --> 00:12:22.166
He's not coming.

251
00:12:23.583 --> 00:12:25.500
